# sigil-manager environment configuration
# ============================================
# Copy this file to `.env` and replace every placeholder. The Go binary loads
# config via `internal/config.Load()` which reads these variables directly
# from the process environment; how you populate the env (direnv, systemd
# EnvironmentFile, docker --env-file, dotenv-cli, etc.) is your choice.
#
# Reference: docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-16-fleet-api-contract.md §F2 (auth),
#            docs/superpowers/specs/2026-05-16-ui-ux-design.md §9 (single admin).
#
# Required vs. optional is enforced by config.Load(); the process refuses to
# start if any required var is unset.

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# HTTP listen address. Optional, default ":8080".
# LISTEN_ADDR=:8080

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Fleet client (consumes Ju571nK/sigil sigil-server)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Base URL of the sigil-server `/v1/*` API. Required UNLESS MOCK_FLEET=1.
# No trailing slash.
SIGIL_SERVER_BASE_URL=http://localhost:9090

# Bearer token sigil-server validates per contract F2. Required UNLESS MOCK_FLEET=1.
# Generate / rotate on the sigil-server side via the SIGIL_SERVER_READ_TOKEN env
# var on THAT process. Both sides must agree.
SIGIL_SERVER_READ_TOKEN=replace-with-your-shared-secret

# Set to "1" to bypass the HTTP FleetClient and use an in-process Mock with
# deterministic fixtures. Useful for local dev without a running sigil-server.
# Optional, default "0".
# MOCK_FLEET=0

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Triage state (sigil-manager-owned SQLite per UI/UX D5)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Path to the SQLite database file holding ack/assign/resolve/notes state.
# Optional, default "./var/triage.sqlite". The directory MUST be writable.
# TRIAGE_DB_PATH=./var/triage.sqlite

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Single-admin auth (UI/UX §9)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Login username for the single admin. Required.
ADMIN_USERNAME=admin

# Bcrypt hash of the admin password. Required.
#
# Must start with "$2a$", "$2b$", or "$2y$" and be 60 chars long.
# The default below is the bcrypt hash of "change-me-on-first-boot" — REPLACE
# IT BEFORE EXPOSING THE CONSOLE TO ANYTHING.
#
# Generate a new hash with:
#   docker run --rm pajlada/bcrypt-cli 'your-password'
# or in Go:
#   import "golang.org/x/crypto/bcrypt"
#   h, _ := bcrypt.GenerateFromPassword([]byte("your-password"), 10)
ADMIN_PASSWORD_BCRYPT=$2a$10$55LlvKwbVdEZOVEdFBFshuFyd1fqHDSKTTXgK5L890cxNNZxATtg2

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# JWT session
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Secret used to HS256-sign session JWTs. Required.
#
# Must be at least 32 bytes (256 bits). Generate one with:
#   openssl rand -base64 32
# Keep it secret — anyone who knows it can forge sessions.
JWT_SECRET=replace-this-with-a-32-byte-or-longer-secret

# Session lifetime in hours. Optional, default 12 (per UI/UX §9).
# JWT_TTL_HOURS=12

# Local-dev only: set to "1" to clear the Secure flag on the session cookie
# so it survives over plain http://. Defaults to Secure=true in production.
# DO NOT set this in any environment reachable from the internet.
# SIGIL_INSECURE_COOKIE=0

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# SPA hints (informational; surfaced via /api/v1/meta)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# How often the SPA polls /api/v1/fleet/events while the Alerts queue is
# visible (UI/UX §7.2). Optional, default 5. Also used as the fleet read
# cache's freshness TTL (see below).
# FLEET_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS=5

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Fleet read cache
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# sigil-manager caches sigil-server read responses in-process so that N
# concurrent dashboard clients do not multiply onto the upstream. The cache is
# stale-while-revalidate with single-flight: entries are fresh for
# FLEET_POLL_INTERVAL_SECONDS, served stale (and refreshed in the background)
# for up to 12× that, and degrade to the last-known-good value if sigil-server
# is briefly unavailable. /v1/healthz is never cached. Triage state is joined
# after the cache, so it is always live.

# Set to "1" to disable the cache entirely (pass-through to sigil-server on
# every request). Optional, default "0". A safe kill-switch.
# FLEET_CACHE_DISABLED=0

# Maximum number of distinct cached (endpoint + filter) keys. Oldest entries
# are evicted past this bound. Optional, default 512.
# FLEET_CACHE_MAX_ENTRIES=512
